</taxonomicName>
there is a female (“P.I.: Luzon / 
<collectingRegion country="Philippines" name="Camarines Sur" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Camarines Sur</collectingRegion>
/ Mt. Isarog, Pili / 
<quantity box="[455,532,560,586]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[545,679,560,586]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" value="1965-04-30">30.IV.1965</date>
”, “H.M. Torrevillas / Collector / Bishop”, coll BPBM, which cannot be 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[311,515,597,625]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[311,326,599,625]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[341,368,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis box="[376,515,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because its vertex is wider. This specimen is possibly the female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflata" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[1324,1339,599,625]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1354,1381,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">) inflata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[271,364,635,661]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but as even the males of these similar species are very difficult to distinguish from each other without reference to genitalia the identity of this female remains doubtful.
</paragraph>
